
SOURCE

http://news.mit.edu/2017/using-machine-learning-improve-patient-care-0821

AGENT

CSAIL

GOAL

To predict patient outcomes in hospitals; to determine what kinds of treatments are needed for different symptoms.

DATA

Large amounts of intensive-care-unit data, from vitals and labs to notes and demographics.

METHODS

The system uses deep learning to make real-time predictions, learning from past ICU cases to make suggestions for critical care, while also explaining the reasoning behind these decisions.

RESULTS

Patients relieved of ailments quicker and diagnosed with more accuracy

COMMENTS

This technology is still in early development. Along with quick diagnosis this technology could potentially be an aid for doctors in the ICU, which is a high-stress, high-demand environment.
